1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e5 4. Nc3 d6 5. e4 Be7
{ Next, you will find three inspirational games in the three of White's main setups to give you an idea about what the Czech Benoni is all about.  Fianchetto Variation: RubiChess vs. Leela Chess Zero  Modern setup: Shakhriyar Mamedyarov vs. Ben Finegold  Classical: Jan Markos vs. Ni Hua }
