1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e5 4. dxe6 fxe6 5. g3
{ This is the most common move at the master level. However, Black has no problems at all because of his control over the center. }
5... Nc6 6. Bg2 d5 { Black threatens to play ...d4. } 7. Nh3
{ A@@EndBracket@@  7.Nc3  d4  8.Ne4  e5  Black is already slightly better. We are ready to answer Nxf6+ with ...gxf6. Our space advantage and better pieces will make the difference.   B@@EndBracket@@  7.e3  White wants to prevent d4.  7...d4  We play ...d4 anyway.  8.exd4  cxd4  .  We have better control over the center. Next, we want to finish our development with ...Be7/d6 and ...O-O.   C@@EndBracket@@  7.cxd5  exd5  .  Our central pawns are strong. Next, we want to finish our development with ...Be7/...Bd6 and ...O-O. }
7... d4
{ Black is already slightly better. He has a space advantage and well-developed pieces. The moves ...Bd6 and ...e5 are coming next.  Themodel game will give you an idea about how the game could continue. }
