1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e5 4. Nc3 d6 5. e4 Be7 6. Nf3 Nbd7 7. Be2
{ If White surprises you with something different than 8.O-O or 9.a3/9.Ne1, there is no reason to panic. We continue with our plans. You will find two model games:  Computer Hiarcs - Seirawan, Yasser, 0-1, 1996.
Nielsen, Peter Heine - Carlsen, Magnus, 0-1, 2007. }
