{ White wants to keep his bishop on h6 and argues we can take it because the h6-pawn would be too strong. But he is wrong. }
14... Nxh6 15. gxh6 Ne8
{ We should not be scared of the h6-pawn. Our e7-bishop is here to control the dark squares while White's dark-squared bishop is missing. ...f5 is coming next and we are ready to play on the queenside too. }
