1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e5 4. Nc3 d6 5. e4 Be7 6. h3 O-O 7. Nf3 Nbd7 8. g4 Ne8
9. Bd3 g6
{ Trying to use our typical plan. But the position is already difficult for Black. }
10. Be3 Ng7 11. Rg1 Nf6 12. Qe2 h5 { Trying to undermine the h3 + g4 pawns. }
13. Nd2 { But White does nothing, and he is right. } 13... Qd7 14. f3 Nh7 15.
O-O-O Bg5 16. Bxg5 Nxg5
{ Black succeeds in trading his bad bishop. But the position is already hopeless. White's attack is too strong. }
17. Qg2 Qe7 18. h4 Nh7 19. Qg3 a6 20. g5 f6 21. gxf6 Rxf6 22. Rdf1 Bd7 23. f4
exf4 24. Rxf4 Rxf4 25. Qxf4 Rf8 26. Qh6 Be8 27. e5
{ The game was already lost, but this move is the final shot. } 27... Qxe5 28.
Bxg6 Bxg6 29. Qxg6 Kh8 30. Nce4 { Everyone joins the party. } 30... Nf5 31.
Qxh5 Nd4 32. Qxe5+ dxe5 { This endgame is just lost. } 33. Rg6 Rf4 34. Rb6 Rxh4
35. b3 Rh1+ 36. Kb2 Rh2 37. Rxb7 Ng5 38. Ka3 Nxe4 39. Nxe4 { Black resigns. } *

