[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Theory 2: Model Games "]
[Black "Lautier, Joel (2678) vs. Nisipeanu, Liviu Dieter (2673)"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e5 4. Nc3 d6 5. e4 Be7 6. Nf3 O-O
{ 6...Nbd7  is my recommendation in the theory section because White could have played h3 followed by g4. }
7. h3 { This is what we want to avoid because White can follow with g4. } 7...
Nbd7 8. Bd3 { However, White decided to play with Bd3. } 8... a6
{ This does nothing against g4.   8...Nh5  with the idea to jump on f4 against g4 is best. }
9. a4 Nh5 10. Ne2
{ A good move. White is overprotecting the f4-square and wants to play g4. }
10... g6
{ Black is ready to meet g4 with ...Ng7 and our typical regrouping plan. } 11.
g4 Ng7 { Black is going for our typical plan. } 12. Ng3 Kh8 13. Be3 Nf6 14. Qc2
Ng8 15. Ke2 Bd7 16. b4 cxb4 17. a5 f5 { Time to break through! } 18. gxf5 gxf5
19. exf5 Bh4 20. Ne4 { Best was  20.Nxh4  Qxh4  . } 20... Nxf5
{ Next, Black wants to activate his g8-knight and take control over the g-file. }
21. Rag1 Nf6 22. Bb6 Qe8 { The queen is ready to join the attack via h5. } 23.
Nxh4 Nxh4 24. Nxd6 Qh5+ 25. Kf1 { The king looks misplaced here. } 25... Rg8
{ Black fights for the control of the g-file. } 26. Be2 Rxg1+ 27. Rxg1
{ 27...Kxg1  is well met by   27...Qg5+  28.Bg4  Rf8  and White's is in trouble. }
27... Bxh3+ 28. Ke1 Bg4
{ Black wants to exchange the main defender of the White's king. } 29. Rxg4
Nxg4 { White wants to use the pin against the g4-knight. } 30. Qe4 Rg8 31. Bc7
Rg7 { Black prevents the Nf7+ threat. Now, the queen is free to move. } 32. Bd8
b3 { A good move! White has to be careful on both sides of the board. } 33. Kd2
{ This allows the queen to join the queenside. } 33... Qh6+ 34. Kc3 Qxd6 35.
Bxh4 Qa3 36. Bd3 { 36.Bxg4  is well met with  36...b2+  . } 36... b2+ 37. Kd2
Qxa5+ 38. Ke2 Qb6 39. Qf5 Qg6 { Black is fine with simplification. } 40. Qf8+
Rg8 41. Qb4 Qh5 42. Bg3 Nxf2+ { The final blow. } 43. Kxf2 Qg5
{ The bishop is lost and the game too. White resigns. A very instructive game by our Czech Benoni's Super Hero. }
