[Round "?"]
[White "Theory 3: 6.Nge2!?"]
[Black "Fyllingen, Roy Harald vs. Jansa, Vlastimil"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e5 4. Nc3 d6 5. e4 Be7 6. Nge2
{ This is a tricky move you should be aware of. White doesn't plan to castle but to play Ng3 followed by h4. That is why Black should not castle too soon and prevent White's plan instead. }
6... O-O
{ That was premature. White is now ready to execute his plan and launch an attack against Black's king. }
7. Ng3
{ Black wants to use our standard regrouping plan. The problem is that this only helps White. }
7... Ne8 8. h4 a6
{ This time, Black doesn't help White with ...g6. Instead, he tries to find counterplay with ...b5. }
9. a4 { White prevents ...b5. } 9... b6 10. Bd3 Ra7
{ Black is squeezed and has trouble to develop his pieces. } 11. Qf3
{ White prepares Nf5.   11.Nf5  was fine.  11...Bxf5  is strongly met with  12.exf5  .  Now the e4-square is available for White's pieces @@StartBracket@@probably the knight@@EndBracket@@ while g4 is coming. }
11... h6 12. Nf5 Bxf5 13. exf5 { Black's position is already lost. } 13... Nd7
14. Ne4
{ A mistake. Black is now able to trade this powerful knight.   14.g4  was best.  14...Ndf6  15.g5  . And in case of @@StartFEN@@3qnrk1/r2nbpp1/pp1p3p/2pPpP2/P1P3PP/2NB1Q2/1P3P2/R1B1K2R b KQ - 0 14@@EndFEN@@  14...Bxh4  15.Qh3  Bg5  16.Bxg5  Qxg5  17.Ne4  Qf4  18.g5  Black has big problems. }
14... Nef6 15. Ra3 Nxe4 16. Bxe4
{ Black succeeded in trading the good pieces. White is only slightly better. }
16... Nf6 17. Qe2 Rb7 18. Bc2 Nh7 19. Rah3
{ White wants to break through with g4-g5. } 19... b5 20. g4
{ White finds the right plan. } 20... f6 21. g5 fxg5 22. f6
{ A strong move! White opens the b1-h7 diagonal. The queen is ready to go on e4. }
22... Bxf6 { 22...Nxf6  23.hxg5  and Black's position collapses. } 23. Qe4 g6
{ The only move. } 24. Qxg6+ Rg7 25. Qxh6 gxh4 26. Qh5
{ 26.Bg6  was best. White wants to play Qh5 next followed by Bh6. } 26... Ng5
27. Bf5 Rff7 { The final blunder. } 28. Rg3 { A strong move. } 28... Kf8
{ 28...hxg3  of course is not possible because of checkmate.  29.Qh8. } 29.
Rxh4 Qa5+
{ 29...Nf3+  is well met with  30.Rxf3  Bxh4  31.Bh6  31...Bf6  32.Bg6  32...Ra7  33.Bxg7+  33...Rxg7   33...Kxg7  34.Qh7+  Kf8  35.Qh8+  Ke7  36.Qxf6+  34.Rxf6+  Qxf6  35.Qh8+  Ke7  36.Qe8 }
30. Kf1 Qxa4 31. Bxg5 Bxg5 32. Rxg5
{ Black resigns.   White was rated 2295 and Black 2520. I hope those games convinced you to push Harry, preventing White's plan, instead of ignoring the danger by castling kingside. }
*

