[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Theory 4: Model Games "]
[Black "Gajewski, Grzegorz vs. Andreikin, Dmitry"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e5 4. Nc3 d6 5. e4 Nbd7 6. Nf3
{ White plays Nf3 first. We must be ready to transpose in the Classical setup  (Nf3 + Be2)  or the Modern main line  (Nf3 + Bd3)  if necessary. }
6... Be7 7. g3 { The Fianchetto Variation. } 7... a6
{ That is the move I recommend in the theory section. We are threatening to play ...b5 if White continues with Bg2. }
8. a4 O-O
{ Now Black's plan is simple. We want to execute our typical regrouping plan: ...Ne8, ...g6, ...Ng7, ...Kh8. You should be well acquainted with this plan by now. }
9. Bg2 Ne8 10. O-O g6 11. Ne1 Ng7 { 11...f5  was fine too. } 12. Nd3 f5 13. f4
Bf6
{ The bishop is well placed on f6. Black is ready to take control over the e5-square and the h8-a1 diagonal. }
14. exf5 gxf5 15. fxe5 Nxe5 16. Nxe5 Bxe5 17. Bf4 Re8
{ Black wants to have a piece on e5. } 18. Qd2 Qf6
{ Adding more control over the e5-square. } 19. Bxe5 Rxe5 20. Ra3 b6 21. Rb3
Qd8 22. Qh6 Ra7 23. Rf4 Ne8
{ The knight was misplaced on g7 and is ready to relocate on f6. The a7-rook can help on g7 or f7. }
24. Rh4 Rg7 25. Bf3 Nf6 26. Qf4 Ng4 27. a5
{ Trying to find some counterplay, but the position is already difficult for White.   27.Bxg4  would help Black to have access to the weak White's king.  27...fxg4  28.a5  Rf7  . }
27... bxa5 28. Bxg4 fxg4 29. Ne4 Rf7
{ The queen is ready to come on f8 with an irresistible attack against White's king. }
30. Rxg4+ { White tries to complicate the game by creating chaos. } 30... Bxg4
31. Qxg4+ Kh8 32. h4 a4 33. Re3 Qg8
{ There are two ways to realize the advantage for Black: Exchanging the queens or to mate White's king. }
34. Qe2 Rfe7 35. Qf3 Qg7 36. Kg2 Re8 37. h5 h6 38. Qf4 Rf8 39. Qh4 Qe7
{ Trying to exchange queens again. White is under psychological pressure. } 40.
Qg4 Qg7 { Again. } 41. Qe2 Rfe8 42. g4
{ Too much pressure and White blunders an important pawn. } 42... Rxh5
{ White resigns. } *

