1. d4 c5 2. d5 d6 3. c4 e5 4. e4 Be7 5. Nf3 Nf6 6. Nc3 Nbd7 7. g3 O-O 8. Bg2
Ne8 { Starting our typical regrouping plan. } 9. O-O g6
{ The knight will support the ...f5 break from g7. } 10. Bh6 Ng7 11. Qd2 Nf6
{ Black wants to harass the h6-bishop with ...Ng4. } 12. h3
{ White prevents ...Ng4. } 12... Kh8
{ The knight will harass the bishop from g8. } 13. Ne1 Ng8
{ The bishop has to make a choice. } 14. Be3 f5 { Time to break through! } 15.
Nd3 Nf6 16. f4 { Premature. White has a problem with the h3-pawn. } 16... Nxe4
17. Nxe4 fxe4 18. Bxe4 Bxh3 { Black is a pawn up. } 19. Bxg6
{ Moving the f1-rook was best. White didn't see Black's last move in his calculation. }
19... Bxf1 20. Qh2 { White is threatening checkmate but now comes } 20... Bh4
{ Interference! } 21. Rxf1 hxg6 { And Black is winning. } 22. fxe5 Rxf1+ 23.
Kxf1 dxe5
{ 23...Nf5  was best.  24.Bf2  Qg5  25.gxh4  Qd2  26.Qh3  Rf8  everyone joins the party and White's king has no chance.  27.exd6  Nxd6  . }
24. Nxc5 Rc8 25. Qxh4+
{ That just helps Black but he has to be careful not to exchange too many pawns in the endgame. }
25... Qxh4 26. gxh4 Nf5 27. Bf2 b6 28. Nd7 Rxc4 29. Nxe5 Rc1+ 30. Kg2 Kg7 31.
Kf3 Rd1 32. Nc6 a6 33. Ke4 { 33.Bxb6  Rxd5 } 33... b5 34. h5 Nd6+ 35. Ke5 Nf7+
36. Ke6 Ng5+ { 36...gxh5  was simple and best. } 37. Ke7 Rxd5 38. Bd4+ Kh6 39.
hxg6 Kxg6 { Now, this endgame requires precise technique. } 40. Bc3 Ne4 41. Bh8
Kf5 42. Nb4 Rd6 43. Nc2 Kf4 44. a3 Rd2 45. Nb4 Nc5 46. Bc3 Rd7+ 47. Ke8 Rd1 48.
Ke7 Kf5 49. Nc6 Rd7+ 50. Ke8 Rh7 { The king is cut off. } 51. Bd4 Nb7 52. Nb4
Nd6+ 53. Kd8
{ And mate is inevitable.   53.Kf8  was best. The game could have continued:  53...a5  54.Nc6  Rf7+  55.Kg8  a4  56.Bc3  Rc7  57.Nd4+  Kg6  58.Ne6  Rc8+  59.Nf8+  Kf5  60.Kg7  Rc7+  61.Kg8  Ne4  62.Ba5  Nf6+  63.Kh8  Rc2  64.Kg7  Rxb2  65.Kf7  Rb3  66.Ne6   66.Bb4  Rxb4  67.axb4  a3  66...Rd3  67.Nc5  Rxa3  68.Bb4  Re3  and the a-pawn will become a queen. }
53... Ke6 *

