3. Nf3 { This is the most common move to avoid 3.d5. } 3... cxd4 4. Nxd4 e5 5.
Nb5
{ The only move to fight for an advantage.  5.Nc2  d5  , @@StartFEN@@rnbqkb1r/pp1p1ppp/5n2/4p3/2PN4/8/PP2PPPP/RNBQKB1R w KQkq - 0 5@@EndFEN@@  5.Nb3  d5  , @@StartFEN@@rnbqkb1r/pp1p1ppp/5n2/4p3/2PN4/8/PP2PPPP/RNBQKB1R w KQkq - 0 5@@EndFEN@@  5.Nf3  Nc6  6.Nc3  Bb4  and Black is fine. }
5... d5 { We will sacrifice a pawn in exchange for a lead in development. } 6.
cxd5 Bc5
{ Black is ready to castle next. In this position, there is one main move which can be trained in the next variation. }
