{ White attacks our c5-bishop. } 12... b6
{ Setting a trap. In this position, White has to play  13.O-O  or  13.Nbc3  .  Then we can move our c5-bishop. We have ideas like ...Ba6, Qe8-h5 to build an attack. We will see what to do if White falls for our trap. }
13. Nxc5 { This is a blunder. } 13... Nxc5 14. O-O Ba6 15. Re1 Qf6
{ And there is too much pressure against f2. } *

