1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. e3
{ This is the second most common move. Here, I recommend we transpose to the Panov Variation of the Caro-Kann Defense. White will have to play with an Isolated Queen Pawn @@StartBracket@@IQP@@EndBracket@@. This is not something you will meet often. That is why my goal is to keep things simple by recommending you simple lines and ideas. }
