{ And Black has no problems. Qb3 and Bc4 are well met with ...Nb6 or ...Nxc3.  A typical plan is to target the c3-pawn  (and the c4-square)  after ...Nxc3.   We can develop as follows: ...O-O, ...Qc7, ...Nc6, ...Rac8. Then, we can take control over the c4-square with the typical maneuver ...Na5-c4.  I recommend you to find different games from this position to understand how to apply this plan. There are two games I'd like to recommend:   Hebden, M. @@StartBracket@@2523@@EndBracket@@ - Anand, V. @@StartBracket@@2793@@EndBracket@@, 0-1, 2014 Nakamura, H @@StartBracket@@2787@@EndBracket@@ - Giri, A. @@StartBracket@@2782@@EndBracket@@, 0-1, 2016 }
