{ Next, you will find 15 models games by club players. I recommend you to play 'guess the moves' with each game.  Studying those games will help you to understand typical mistakes by White such as:  - castling too early;  - not preventing ...h5-h4;  - premature f4, allowing Black to take control over the e5-square.  The commentary is more succinct.   Here, I want you to develop your feel for the opening. You should try to intuit Black's moves and punish White's ones.  Notes: Do not consider all Black's moves as best. You must be ready to criticize Black's play, notably if he misplayed the opening partly because of wrong move order.  Good luck! }
