1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e5 4. Nc3 d6 5. e4 Be7 6. Bd3 Nbd7 7. Be3
{ White waits. Here my recommendation would be to play  7...h5  . } 7... Nf8
{ Black's idea is to play ...Ng6 and ...h5. } 8. f3 h5 9. Qd2
{ White should have prevented ...h5-h4 by playing h4 himself. } 9... Ng6
{ 9...h4  ,  preventing White to play h4 himself was best. } 10. Nge2
{ Again, White should have prevented the ...h5-h4 idea. } 10... h4 11. O-O-O
{ The ...b5 breakthrough will be stronger now Black has a clear target on c1. }
11... a6 12. g4 Nh7 13. h3 Bd7 14. Rdf1 b5
{ Black is already slightly better. The plan is to open the b-file and to trade the e7-bishop. }
15. Rh2 O-O 16. Kb1 Rb8 17. Nd1 bxc4 18. Bxc4 Bb5 19. Qd3 Rb7 20. Bc1 Qb6
{ White is under pressure, ...Rfb8 and ...Bg5 are coming next. } 21. Rg2 Bg5
22. Qc2 Rfb8 23. b3 { This creates a hook. } 23... a5
{ Black is ready to open White's queenside. } 24. Nb2 a4 25. Nc3 Bxc4 26. Nxc4
axb3 27. axb3 Qa6 28. Nd1 Rxb3+ 29. Bb2 R8b4
{ The c4-knight is under attack. But the knight can't move because of ...Ra3-a1. White resigns. }
