1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e5 4. Nc3 d6 5. e4 Be7 6. Be2 O-O 7. f4
{ This is premature and will give Black control over the e5-square. } 7... exf4
8. Bxf4 Nbd7 9. Nf3 Nh5
{ Black wants to take the f4-bishop and play ...Bf6, ...Ne5 next. } 10. Be3 g6
{ The knight is ready to jump on g7. } 11. Bh6 Ng7 12. O-O Bf6 13. Qd2 Ne5
{ Black realized his plan. } 14. Ng5 Bg4 15. Nf3 Bd7 16. Bf4 Qe7
{ This gives more support to the e5-square. } 17. Nxe5 Bxe5 18. Bxe5 Qxe5 19.
Qf4 Rae8 { Black is ready to take on e5 with the rook. } 20. Qxe5 Rxe5 21. Rf2
f6 { This is passive.  21...f5  was best. } 22. Raf1 Ne8
{ Black is forced to defend the f6-pawn. } 23. Bd3 Kg7 24. Nb1 g5 25. h3 h5 26.
Nd2 g4 27. hxg4 hxg4 28. g3 a6 { The ...b5 rupture is coming. } 29. Rf4 b5 30.
a3 Kg6 31. R1f2 Ng7 32. Rg2 Nh5 33. Rff2 Rb8 34. cxb5 axb5 35. b4 c4 36. Bc2
Kg5 37. Nb1 { Black is ready to break with ...f5. The a3-pawn is a weakness. }
37... Ra8 38. Re2 f5 { White is lost. } 39. exf5 Rxe2 40. Rxe2 Nxg3
{ There is nothing for White to hope for in this endgame. } 41. Re7 Bxf5 42.
Bxf5 Kxf5 43. Kf2 Ne4+ 44. Ke3 Nf6 45. Kd4 g3 { Garry decides the game. } 46.
Re3 g2 47. Re1 Kg4 48. Nc3 Rxa3 { White resigns. } *

