1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e5 4. Nc3 d6 5. e4 Be7 6. f4
{ This is premature. Black will take control over the e5-square. } 6... exf4 7.
Bxf4 O-O 8. Bd3 Bg4 9. Nge2 Nh5 { Black wants to win the important bishop. }
10. O-O Nxf4 11. Rxf4 { Black is ready to take control over the e5-square. }
11... Bxe2 12. Qxe2
{ Black trades his good bishop for a knight. But the important is the remaining pieces:   White's bishop is bad. Black's bishop will be useful. }
12... Nd7 13. e5
{ White tries a typical pawn sacrifice to activate his knight on e4. But this doesn't work here. }
13... Nxe5 14. Ne4 f5 { The knight is unstable on e4. } 15. Nxc5
{ Black's position was already strategically lost. This is the final blunder. }
15... Qb6 16. b4 Nxd3 { White resigns. } 17. Qxd3 { 17.Qxe7  Nxf4 } 17... dxc5
