{ This allows Black to trade his bad bishop. } 9... Bg5 10. Nd3 Nd7 11. f4
{ This is premature and gives Black control over the e5-square. } 11... exf4
12. Bxf4 Bxf4 13. Rxf4 Qe7 14. Qd2 Ne5
{ Black is ready to establish a strong blockade on d6 with his knight. } 15.
Nxe5 dxe5 16. Rf2 Nd6 17. Bd3 Bd7 { Black is ready to meet Nb5 with ...Bxb5. }
18. Raf1 f5 19. g3 Rf7 20. a3 a5 21. b3 Raf8 22. Qe3 b6 23. Kh1 Re8 24. a4 Qf8
25. Nb5 Bxb5 26. axb5
{ White is left with the bad bishop against the good knight. } 26... Ree7 27.
exf5 gxf5 28. Qg5+ Rg7 29. Qh5 e4 { The bishop is kicked. } 30. Bb1 Ref7
{ The f5-pawn is protected. Black is ready to take control over the e5-square with his queen. }
31. Qh6 Qe7 32. Qe3 Qe5 33. Rd2 Rg6 34. Bc2 a4 { A strong move. } 35. Bd1 Rgg7
{ 35...axb3  was best.  36.Bxb3  Ra7  37.Ra2  Rxa2  38.Bxa2  Qd4  . } 36. Bh5
Ra7 37. Bd1 a3 38. Ra2 Ra8 39. Rff2 Qd4 40. Qe1 e3 41. Rf3 Re7 42. Bc2 e2
{ Black is threatening to play ...Qb2. } 43. Bd3
{ There was nothing to do against Black's threat. } 43... Qb2
{ The final blow. } 44. Bb1 { 44.Rxb2  axb2 } 44... Qxb1 { White resigns. } *

