1... a5
{ Congrats if you found this one. We want to use our typical plan from the King's Indian Defense. However, it is important to always think about what are the ideas of the opponent.  White wants to play a5 and take advantage of our unprotected rook on a8. Because of the position of our bishop on e7, White also has ideas of Nxe5!, ...dxe5, d6! That is why Black needs to push a5 himself. Black is now ready to continue with his plan.   1...h5  ,  starting to launch an attack with a pawn avalanche is a mistake because of  2.a5  2...Bd7  3.Nxe5  ,  a crushing move.  3...dxe5  4.d6  . }
*

