[SetUp "1"]

{ What to do? } 1... Bf8
{ Nice!   In the game, Black played  1...Bxd3  first  but now came:  2.Bxd3  Bf8  3.g5  Bxh6  4.gxh6  and the knight is lost because of the mate threat on g7. The game continued  4...Qf8  5.Raf1  Qxh6  6.Rxf6  Qe3+  7.R6f2  Rxf2  8.Rxf2  Rf8  9.Bf5!  Black resigned as ...Qxc3 is met with Be6+. }
2. Bg5 { 2.Bxf8  Bxd3  and Black has no problems. } 2... Bxd3 3. Bxd3
{ What now? } 3... Nxd5 { Never forget our typical trap! } 4. Bxd8 Nxc3 5. Rxf7
Kxf7 6. Rf1+ Kg8 { And Black will save the knight via a4! } *

