{ What is the best way to recapture the pawn?  Sorry for the disturbance and hoping it will help someone incompetent like me not to lose 1 hour and a half of his life :@@EndBracket@@ }
1... e4 { Sorry if I tricked you! First, we want to bring the queen on e4! } 2.
Qxe4 Bf6 { Then we improve the position of our bishop with tempo. } 3. Ra2
{ 3.Rb1  Bxf5  , while @@StartFEN@@1rbq1rk1/6np/pn1p1bp1/2pP1P2/P1P1Q3/5NP1/4NPBP/R1B1R1K1 w - - 1 3@@EndFEN@@  3.Ra3  is similar to the game.  3...Bxf5  4.Qf4  Nh5  5.Qh6  Bg7  6.Qg5  Nxc4  with a decisive advantage. }
3... Bxf5 { And only now we take on f5 with our bishop. } 4. Qf4 Bb1
{ A beautiful move. The rook has trouble finding a good square. } 5. Ra3 Nh5 6.
Qh6 Bg7 7. Qe3 Nxc4 8. Qe6+ Kh8 { The rook has no square. } 9. Rc3
{ White wants to find compensation on the dark squares after ...Bxc3. } 9...
Bf5 { But we are more interested in the queen. } *

